    <div class="nd"><div class="ndot"></div><span class="nname">+22 nodes/vps</span></div>
  </div>

  <div class="panel-grid g2" style="margin-bottom:2px">
    <div class="panel">
      <div class="p-lbl">Layer 0  Edge</div>
      <div class="p-title">Cloudflare + NGINX Multi-Tenant Routing</div>
      <div class="p-body">
        All inbound traffic passes through Cloudflare before reaching origin. NGINX
        server blocks are generated programmatically  one upstream per tenant, no
        config sharing across instances. SSL termination at proxy layer with automated
        lifecycle management. ModSecurity OWASP CRS deployed and tuned per host.
        Paranoia levels calibrated to minimize false positives without reducing protection.
      </div>
      <div class="tags">
        <span class="tag">Cloudflare WAF</span>
        <span class="tag">NGINX</span>
        <span class="tag red">ModSecurity OWASP CRS</span>
        <span class="tag">SSL Lifecycle</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="panel">
      <div class="p-lbl">Layer 1  Container Fleet</div>
      <div class="p-title">Isolated Docker Compose Fleets</div>
      <div class="p-body">
        100&ndash;200 Docker Compose stacks per host running web application workloads
        including PHP-based CMS, custom applications, and Supabase-backed services.
        Each container runs its own PHP-FPM process pool, isolated volume mounts, and
        dedicated or shared managed DB. Pools tiered by traffic class. No shared
        runtime between tenants. Health checks automated. Images hardened and version-pinned.
      </div>
      <div class="tags">
        <span class="tag">Docker Compose</span>
        <span class="tag">PHP-FPM Tiering</span>
        <span class="tag violet">Supabase</span>
        <span class="tag amber">Managed DB</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="panel-grid g2" style="margin-bottom:40px">
    <div class="panel">
      <div class="p-lbl">Layer 2  Automation</div>
      <div class="p-title">Ansible + Semaphore Fleet Orchestration</div>
      <div class="p-body">
        All fleet operations  SSL renewal, container restarts, backup triggers,
        application updates, security rule deployments  driven by Ansible playbooks
        executed through Semaphore UI. YAML inventory maps server roles to targeted host
        groups. Color-coded logging surfaces failures without noise. All playbooks are
        Git-versioned and idempotent. No manual per-server operations at this fleet scale.
      </div>
      <div class="tags">
        <span class="tag">Ansible</span>
        <span class="tag">Semaphore UI</span>
        <span class="tag">YAML Inventory</span>
        <span class="tag blue">Git-Versioned</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="panel">
      <div class="p-lbl">Layer 3  Observability</div>
      <div class="p-title">Full-Stack Monitoring Pipeline</div>
      <div class="p-body">
        cAdvisor exposes per-container CPU, memory, and network metrics. Node Exporter
        covers host-level resource utilization. Prometheus scrapes both, feeding Grafana
        dashboards built for container-dense environments. Loki aggregates application
        and access logs for cross-host querying. Matomo analytics deployed across multiple
        instances with managed DB topology and Cloudflare edge caching on tracker
        endpoints. Kuma handles per-service uptime monitoring.
      </div>
      <div class="tags">
        <span class="tag">Prometheus</span>
        <span class="tag">Grafana</span>
        <span class="tag blue">Loki</span>
        <span class="tag">cAdvisor</span>
        <span class="tag">Node Exporter</span>
        <span class="tag violet">Matomo</span>
        <span class="tag">Kuma</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

